article.headline: Illinois 89, Chicago St. 50
article.story: CHAMPAIGN, Ill. -- Mike Tisdale had a career-high 25 points and 10 rebounds to lead Illinois to a 89-50 win over Chicago State on Wednesday night. Mike Davis also had a double-double, scoring 11 points and collecting 12 rebounds for Illinois (9-1). Trent Meacham added 14 points and Demetri McCamey finished with 10 for the Illini. The 7-foot-1 Tisdale made the most of a size advantage for Illinois (9-1) up front. The sophomore scored 16 points in the first half to give Illinois a 41-26 lead at the break. Illinois held Chicago State (3-5) to 34 points below their season average and forced the Cougars into 29 turnovers. Chicago State closed to 47-38 in the second half behind two 3-pointers by David Holston. But Illinois pulled away with a 24-5 run. Holston led Chicago State with 17 points. Tawrence Walton had 11 points.
